{
  "doc_id": "54026",
  "text": "Moreover, IL-15 is crucial in the development and maintenance of immune cells. The proliferation, activation and distribution of NK-cells are regulated by IL-15. Similarly to NK-cells, IL-15 modulates CD8 T-cell homeostasis and promotes survival of naïve T-cells as well as proliferation of B-cells [CITATION_1] . NK-cells and CD8 T-cells are necessary for the effective clearance of viral pathogens and the destruction of tumour cells. Consequently, the immune response in IL-15 knockout mice infected with the vaccinia virus was impaired [CITATION_2] . IL-15 is also implicated in the innate immune response by enhancing neutrophil migration and phagocytosis [CITATION_3] .",
